-- Tanzania Police Arrest Four Amid Protests Over New Constitution, News Says
-- B y   W i l f r e d   M w a k a l o s i
-- 2010-12-29T09:50:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-29/tanzania-police-arrest-four-amid-protests-over-new-constitution-news-says.html
Tanzanian police arrested at least
four people and fired shots in the air yesterday to disperse a
demonstration by opposition-party supporters demanding a new
national constitution, the  Daily News  reported.  The gathering took place as the Civic United Front party
presented its proposals on a new charter to Justice and
Constitutional Affairs Permanent Secretary Oliver Mhaiki, the
Dar es Salaam-based newspaper said today.  The opposition wants the constitution changed because the
current document provides too much power to the president, the
newspaper said, citing Julius Mtatiro, acting deputy secretary-
general of the CUF.  In August, neighboring Kenya enacted a new constitution
that aims to place checks on the power of the president, spread
power among the East African nationâ€™s 42 ethnic groups and
distribute land more equitably.  To contact the reporter on this story:
